-- Schneider accepts Carlyle, PAI offer for sensors unit 
-- By James Regan
-- Thu May 15, 2014 12:07PM EDT
-- None



PARIS, May 15 (Reuters) - French electrical gear maker Schneider Electric <SCHN.PA> said it has accepted an offer from private equity groups The Carlyle Group <CG.O> and PAI Partners for its sensors business in a deal based on an enterprise value of $900 million.

Schneider confirmed that it would reinvest about $100 million in the business - Custom Sensors & Technologies (CST) - in order to have a shareholding of about 30 percent.